OBINNA EZUGWU The incumbent Governor of Edo State and candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Mr. Godwin Obaseki won the Edo State governorship election held on Saturday. Obaseki polled a total of 307,955 votes to defeat his closest challenger and candidate of the All Progressive Congress (APC), Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu who scored 223, 619 votes according to the final results announced by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). Having scored the highest number of votes, the INEC returning officer for the election,.. declared Obaseki winner of the polls. The results below:
